Iberia applies cargo fuel surcharge . Spain ' s state airline Iberia has introduced a cargo fuel surcharge of 13 pesetas per kg , equivalent to US $ 10 cents , to cover increased fuel costs , air cargo industry sources told Reuters . The rises apply so far to international routes only and were effective from November 11 , an official at a foreign airline operating said . Iberia cargo spokesmen were not immediately available for comment . The move follows cargo fuel surcharges of US $ 10 cents , or the equivalent in local currencies , announced since October 25 by many airlines led by the main European carriers . - - Air Cargo Newsroom Tel + 44 171 542 7706 Fax + 44 171 542 5017 
